Diagnose common issues with your weg environment.

Checks:
  - devbox installation and configuration
  - Required services (mariadb, redis)
  - Site configuration
  - Asset symlinks
  - Python environment

Examples:
  weg doctor       # Run all checks in current project
  weg doctor -v    # Run with verbose output

Exits non-zero if any check fails, so it can gate scripts and CI.
For system-level compatibility checks, see 'weg self doctor'.

Usage:
  weg doctor [flags]

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for doctor

Global Flags:
  -C, --chdir string              Run as if weg was started in <path>
      --config string             Path to config file (default: auto-detect)
      --debug-categories string   Filter debug output: all,config,state,net,git,fs,exec
      --log-level string          Set log level: quiet, normal, verbose, debug, trace
  -o, --output string             Output format: auto, json, table, plain, quiet (default "auto")
  -q, --quiet                     Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose count             Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
  -y, --yes                       Assume yes for all prompts
